{
  "texts": [
    "For example, applications are expected in fields such as computer-aided diagnosis, data summarization, communication, and education.",
    "[5] [6] [7] [8] [9] [10] [11] [12] To evaluate the performance of LLMs in applications requiring medical expertise, studies have been conducted using medical examinations for undergraduates and postgraduates worldwide.",
    "These evaluations included national medical licensing examinations in Japan [13] [14] [15] and the United States 10, 16 and board certification examinations in neurology, 17 nephrology, 18 family medicine, 19 general surgery, 20 neurosurgery, 21, 22 orthopedic surgery, 23 urology, 24 plastic surgery, 25 obstetrics and gynecology, 26 anesthesiology, 27 radiology, 28 dermatology, 29 ophthalmology, 30 and otorhinolaryngology.",
    "31 Earlier versions of ChatGPT had a correct answer rate of 30%-60%, i.e., mostly failing scores.",
    "However, performance has significantly improved since the release of ChatGPT-4."
  ]
}